WEBVTT

00:15.460 --> 00:19.960
♪During the dark night♪

00:20.100 --> 00:22.750
♪A guiding light♪

00:23.260 --> 00:25.050
♪Just like you♪

00:25.460 --> 00:29.750
♪Makes life turn bright♪

00:30.330 --> 00:35.180
♪Breaking free from darkness♪

00:35.400 --> 00:38.880
♪You gave me strength♪

00:39.230 --> 00:41.780
♪Running for truth♪

00:41.800 --> 00:45.850
♪I find my path♪

00:46.600 --> 00:50.580
♪Drawing on the hope♪

00:51.200 --> 00:54.580
♪That you render me♪

00:55.130 --> 00:58.010
♪In this long journey♪

00:58.260 --> 01:01.680
♪I run on lightly♪

01:19.180 --> 01:22.980
[Reborn]
[Adapted from Qiang Yu's work, Reborn]

01:23.080 --> 01:24.280
I hate my dad.

01:24.760 --> 01:27.280
I hate that all he does

01:27.920 --> 01:29.470
is hurt me and my mom.

01:33.150 --> 01:34.310
But now,

01:36.310 --> 01:37.470
I hate myself even more.

01:38.920 --> 01:40.280
I can't do anything.

01:41.190 --> 01:43.789
I only make everything worse.

01:52.030 --> 01:53.120
Did you know?

01:54.630 --> 01:56.960
I still think that standing up

01:57.310 --> 01:58.800
for Beiyu

01:58.800 --> 02:00.390
was the right thing to do,

02:01.520 --> 02:04.310
but I know what I did
has hurt my family.

02:05.350 --> 02:06.520
That's a fact.

02:08.800 --> 02:10.919
My mom is getting worse.

02:11.430 --> 02:12.920
She's always emotional

02:13.110 --> 02:14.840
and keeps arguing with my dad.

02:15.880 --> 02:18.070
My little brother won't come back
because of this.

02:20.390 --> 02:22.350
I don't even know what to do next.

02:24.390 --> 02:26.030
I used to be so angry.

02:26.600 --> 02:28.360
I thought they were twisting the truth,

02:28.470 --> 02:30.600
refusing to admit their mistakes.

02:32.640 --> 02:34.390
But now I'm not angry anymore.

02:36.470 --> 02:39.390
Does everyone have troubles like this?

02:43.720 --> 02:44.520
Even though

02:45.310 --> 02:47.800
we're not naive anymore.

02:48.600 --> 02:51.079
we still can't solve problems

02:51.110 --> 02:52.470
as easily as adults seem to.

02:53.470 --> 02:54.270
It's hard

02:54.829 --> 02:58.079
to even talk about our problems.

03:02.880 --> 03:05.750
Do you think these problems
will ever go away?

03:05.910 --> 03:06.800
Or will everything

03:07.360 --> 03:09.240
just get better when we grow up?

03:11.360 --> 03:12.360
I don't know either.

03:13.160 --> 03:13.960
This is

03:15.830 --> 03:17.310
my first time growing up.

03:19.880 --> 03:20.960
But I do know

03:21.110 --> 03:23.550
however suffocating
or upsetting things get,

03:24.880 --> 03:26.470
I'll find solace and freedom in dance.

03:26.800 --> 03:28.440
It's where I can truly breathe.

03:30.980 --> 03:35.930
[Episode 16]
[Sister's Wish]

03:39.960 --> 03:40.920
Did you know?

03:42.240 --> 03:43.640
The teachers who train

03:43.640 --> 03:45.390
the best dancers in the world

03:46.110 --> 03:47.150
are mirrors.

03:49.210 --> 03:52.630
♪Under the sunlight♪

03:52.630 --> 03:56.460
♪Birds take a fly♪

03:57.360 --> 03:58.550
In the mirror,

03:59.360 --> 04:01.870
we can take a good look at ourselves,

04:01.870 --> 04:03.040
♪Only you♪

04:03.040 --> 04:04.240
correct ourselves,

04:05.480 --> 04:08.200
and become better versions of ourselves.

04:08.200 --> 04:09.430
♪During the dark night♪

04:09.430 --> 04:12.910
♪A guiding light♪

04:12.910 --> 04:14.530
♪Just like you♪

04:14.530 --> 04:19.480
♪Makes life turn bright♪

04:19.480 --> 04:24.600
♪Breaking free from darkness♪

04:24.600 --> 04:29.390
♪You gave me strength♪

04:29.390 --> 04:31.840
♪Running for truth♪

04:31.840 --> 04:36.880
♪I find my path♪

04:36.880 --> 04:41.110
♪Drawing on the hope♪

04:41.110 --> 04:44.710
♪That you render me♪

04:44.710 --> 04:48.060
♪In this long journey♪

04:48.060 --> 04:52.610
♪I run lightly♪

05:13.060 --> 05:14.560
[Negative]

05:18.080 --> 05:20.390
Here we have the trigonometric formulas.

05:20.830 --> 05:22.800
There are five of them,

05:22.800 --> 05:24.550
and you must memorize them.

05:24.760 --> 05:26.110
Now, let's go over the first problem.

05:26.110 --> 05:29.520
Point A is (1, √5),

05:29.520 --> 05:32.110
and the line y = 2x + 2p
passes through it.

05:32.110 --> 05:34.590
We need to find the distance
from A to the directrix of C.

05:34.590 --> 05:35.870
Remember, we're solving for the distance

05:35.870 --> 05:36.710
to the directrix.

05:36.710 --> 05:38.520
Chen Hao, what are you doing?

05:39.790 --> 05:41.080
Are you asleep?

05:42.120 --> 05:43.080
Stand up.

05:44.000 --> 05:45.030
You've got the notes in your hand,

05:45.030 --> 05:46.000
and you're still dozing off.

05:46.080 --> 05:47.680
Show me if you can sleep while standing.

05:47.909 --> 05:48.710
Ye Zilin!

05:49.760 --> 05:50.909
You're having such a great time.

05:51.120 --> 05:51.960
Teach me.

05:53.000 --> 05:57.030
Is it Y² equals 5X?

05:57.320 --> 05:58.320
You're even connecting trigonometry

05:58.320 --> 06:00.200
to directrix distances.

06:00.200 --> 06:01.390
Amazing!

06:01.390 --> 06:03.230
Well, I mean…

06:03.230 --> 06:04.710
Can't you separate algebra

06:04.710 --> 06:05.320
and geometry?

06:05.760 --> 06:06.470
What's that?

06:06.790 --> 06:08.150
Everyone else, focus on the lecture.

06:08.440 --> 06:09.440
You two, stay standing.

06:09.560 --> 06:11.320
Take notes if you don't understand.

06:11.440 --> 06:13.270
Let's go back to the first question.

06:13.270 --> 06:16.390
Add Y², subtract 2X,
and set it equal to 15, equal to zero.

06:17.030 --> 06:19.030
What does this equation tell us?

06:19.030 --> 06:21.960
[Countdown to NCEE: 50 Days]

06:21.960 --> 06:23.830
Everyone, these three problems

06:23.830 --> 06:25.790
are key and challenging questions
for 12th-grade math.

06:35.940 --> 06:38.940
♪You opened a window♪

06:41.920 --> 06:45.860
♪I saw hope outside the window♪

06:48.040 --> 06:52.070
♪You said something
I couldn't understand♪

06:53.860 --> 06:57.340
♪And I realized my desire♪

07:00.000 --> 07:03.580
♪You lit up a lamp♪

07:06.560 --> 07:10.150
♪I saw the light♪

07:12.400 --> 07:15.850
♪You slowly walked away♪

07:18.450 --> 07:22.100
♪And I realized my helplessness♪

07:24.670 --> 07:28.020
♪Actually, I haven't let go♪

07:30.660 --> 07:34.060
♪It's just a pretense of silence♪

07:36.780 --> 07:39.920
♪How should I find comfort♪

07:40.290 --> 07:41.950
♪In the unknown years ahead?♪

07:42.430 --> 07:47.440
♪Don't be so miserable anymore♪

07:49.080 --> 07:53.560
♪I walk alone
through this heartbreaking street♪

07:53.560 --> 07:55.440
We often believe that what we see

07:55.440 --> 07:56.390
[Mental Health]
is the truth.

07:57.080 --> 07:58.830
When others have different opinions,

07:59.000 --> 08:01.880
we often feel misunderstood and angry.

08:02.270 --> 08:03.470
But honestly,

08:03.470 --> 08:05.030
there's no single right
or wrong answer

08:05.030 --> 08:06.440
when people disagree.

08:08.080 --> 08:09.270
Take this apple for instance.

08:09.590 --> 08:12.120
One side is red,
and the other side is yellow.

08:12.390 --> 08:13.320
From a single perspective,

08:13.320 --> 08:15.270
you'll never see the whole picture.

08:15.390 --> 08:16.590
From different angles,

08:16.590 --> 08:19.640
it appears entirely different.

08:20.470 --> 08:21.960
So, everyone,

08:22.320 --> 08:24.560
try to step out of your own perspective

08:24.710 --> 08:26.150
to understand and communicate.

08:26.520 --> 08:28.000
This is a very important step

08:28.030 --> 08:29.470
on the path to growing up.

08:42.760 --> 08:43.390
By the way,

08:43.559 --> 08:45.200
there's a new comic café near my place.

08:45.320 --> 08:46.590
Let's go this Saturday.

08:46.830 --> 08:47.640
Sure.

08:48.230 --> 08:49.590
But I still have homework to do.

08:50.270 --> 08:51.590
You can do it on Sunday.

08:55.880 --> 08:57.080
Why aren't you saying anything?

08:58.200 --> 08:59.830
Take a look at this.

09:02.450 --> 09:05.750
[The Sorrow That Shouldn't Be Forgotten]

09:07.200 --> 09:08.910
I feel so bad for Qiao Beiyu.

09:12.470 --> 09:13.710
Where's this article from?

09:14.560 --> 09:16.320
Someone posted it on the forum.

09:16.320 --> 09:18.000
Qiao Qingyu ran away
during winter vacation

09:18.000 --> 09:19.760
because she exposed this article

09:19.760 --> 09:20.880
at her cousin's wedding

09:20.880 --> 09:22.000
and ruined the wedding.

09:22.320 --> 09:23.760
How brave of her.

09:24.910 --> 09:27.150
But we mocked her for it.

09:28.680 --> 09:30.120
Do you think we're wrong,

09:30.230 --> 09:32.120
like Ms. Le Fan suggested?

09:32.120 --> 09:33.590
Did we only see one side of the story

09:33.590 --> 09:34.790
and misunderstand Qiao Qingyu?

10:02.080 --> 10:03.710
If you're here to settle scores with me,

10:03.800 --> 10:05.710
I've already gone back,
knelt, and apologized.

10:06.230 --> 10:07.630
If you're here for forgiveness,

10:08.080 --> 10:10.230
the only person in this world
who could forgive you

10:10.230 --> 10:11.280
is already dead.

10:12.350 --> 10:15.920
Qing, I'm leaving Huanzhou.

10:16.630 --> 10:17.960
I came to say goodbye.

10:19.590 --> 10:21.590
I don't know how you feel
about Nanqiao Village.

10:22.590 --> 10:25.510
You and Yu were born
and raised in Shunyun.

10:26.560 --> 10:28.280
Maybe Nanqiao Village

10:29.080 --> 10:30.160
is just a fleeting, unwelcome stop

10:30.160 --> 10:32.080
during your summer and winter vacations.

10:32.990 --> 10:36.200
You don't understand
the intricate relationships

10:36.830 --> 10:37.870
and rules of the village.

10:39.320 --> 10:40.590
But let me tell you something.

10:41.080 --> 10:42.800
Your clarity and courage
come from the fact

10:43.080 --> 10:44.470
that you have a way out.

10:44.800 --> 10:46.440
You can leave at any time

10:47.470 --> 10:48.870
while we can't.

10:54.560 --> 10:56.560
Bei and I depended
on each other completely

10:58.110 --> 10:59.830
as we grew up.

11:00.870 --> 11:01.830
After university,

11:03.280 --> 11:05.200
we got together.

11:07.280 --> 11:10.560
But then our family found out about us.

11:11.350 --> 11:12.960
When she needed me the most,

11:14.400 --> 11:15.630
I backed out.

11:17.040 --> 11:19.440
I fought so hard
to leave Nanqiao Village.

11:19.990 --> 11:22.200
I just didn't have the courage
to give up everything for her.

11:26.320 --> 11:27.870
I won't make excuses for myself.

11:28.680 --> 11:30.870
I deserve the situation
I'm in right now.

11:31.990 --> 11:34.960
Honestly, when you exposed everything,

11:35.710 --> 11:37.110
I felt relieved.

11:37.680 --> 11:39.560
It felt like the massive stone
hanging over me

11:40.280 --> 11:41.710
finally fell.

11:44.350 --> 11:45.830
Thank you, Qing.

11:46.990 --> 11:48.400
You set me free.

11:49.350 --> 11:52.960
And I hope my leaving
will set you free too.

12:02.830 --> 12:04.400
These are all of Beiyu's belongings
that are left.

12:05.630 --> 12:07.470
You're more qualified
to keep it than I am.

12:39.680 --> 12:43.350
Qing, don't let the past trap you.

12:44.110 --> 12:46.320
Finish what Beiyu couldn't.

12:47.230 --> 12:49.200
Live the life Beiyu couldn't.

12:50.080 --> 12:52.160
That's what she'd want most.

14:48.510 --> 14:49.590
All right, everyone.

14:49.590 --> 14:51.350
Our focus today

14:51.350 --> 14:52.960
is the past anterior tense.

14:53.230 --> 14:55.160
Before we dive into it,

14:55.230 --> 14:58.320
let's review what we've learned before.

14:58.320 --> 15:00.800
The compound past tense.

15:00.800 --> 15:03.230
Thank you for last night.

15:03.230 --> 15:04.280
Everyone, repeat after me.

15:04.280 --> 15:05.320
This is the French phrase

15:05.320 --> 15:06.160
for "I love you."

15:06.160 --> 15:08.200
It's "je t'aime."

16:28.470 --> 16:31.750
Wang Mumu,
did you report me to the police?

16:32.040 --> 16:34.040
You ungrateful brat!

16:34.510 --> 16:36.040
Don't you touch me!

16:36.990 --> 16:38.280
What? What are you doing?

16:38.440 --> 16:39.990
Go ahead, hit me!

16:40.560 --> 16:41.470
Move aside!

16:41.750 --> 16:43.750
All you do is cry!

16:44.080 --> 16:45.230
Can you even do anything else but cry?

16:46.230 --> 16:48.040
They're neighbors!
We can't make them pay!

16:48.040 --> 16:49.680
It was just a bowl of noodles!
How much could it cost?

16:49.680 --> 16:51.470
Just a bowl?
They come with their friends.

16:51.470 --> 16:52.830
That's more than one bowl of noodles.

16:52.870 --> 16:54.040
How many times did they come?

16:54.040 --> 16:55.750
They own shops too.

16:55.750 --> 16:56.590
When you buy things from them,

16:56.590 --> 16:58.990
don't they sometimes let you
buy on credit too?

16:58.990 --> 16:59.680
You're mistaken.

16:59.680 --> 17:01.350
I've never bought anything
from their shop.

17:01.350 --> 17:02.750
She's just a gossiper.

17:02.800 --> 17:04.349
Then you should
be even more patient with her.

17:04.630 --> 17:05.400
She's always talking

17:05.400 --> 17:07.160
about the neighbors and their issues.

17:07.440 --> 17:08.400
Why should I?

17:08.400 --> 17:10.160
Don't you know
how to maintain social etiquette?

17:10.160 --> 17:10.920
If you don't cater to her,

17:10.920 --> 17:12.280
she'll spread stories
everywhere about you.

17:12.280 --> 17:13.240
You're the one
who can't keep your mouth shut

17:13.240 --> 17:14.200
and says anything that comes to mind.

17:14.200 --> 17:15.470
How could it be me?

17:15.470 --> 17:17.200
Doesn't she usually help our business?

17:17.200 --> 17:18.280
Who helps your business?

17:18.280 --> 17:19.710
When has she ever helped your business?

17:19.710 --> 17:21.510
I don't know
if she's never helped my business.

17:21.510 --> 17:23.510
But she's bad-mouthed others
behind their backs.

17:23.510 --> 17:24.829
[A Dance Tribute to Qiao Beiyu]
But if she brings people here,

17:24.829 --> 17:26.160
isn't that helping our business?

17:41.350 --> 17:43.230
How's your appetite lately?

17:45.230 --> 17:46.280
It's fine.

17:47.320 --> 17:48.920
Is there anything you want to eat?

17:49.960 --> 17:51.350
Not really.

17:51.870 --> 17:54.400
I'm not sure what's good to eat
during the NCEE season.

17:54.750 --> 17:56.040
Maybe there's something
that helps with concentration.

17:56.040 --> 17:56.750
We can buy it.

17:56.750 --> 17:57.710
Ask your classmates.

17:58.350 --> 18:00.230
The school meals are enough for me.

18:04.080 --> 18:04.870
Oh, shoot!

18:05.920 --> 18:08.080
I left the new receipts behind.

18:08.080 --> 18:09.200
Wait here.

18:19.960 --> 18:22.470
Qingyu, it's been a while
since we last saw each other.

18:22.590 --> 18:24.960
Have you stopped helping in the shop
after school?

18:27.440 --> 18:29.600
Oh, that face of yours.

18:29.600 --> 18:31.120
So dull, neither bright nor pale.

18:31.470 --> 18:32.600
Why are you so gloomy

18:32.600 --> 18:34.030
at your age?

18:34.030 --> 18:35.880
Even the prettiest face
won't look good like that.

18:35.960 --> 18:37.070
None of your business.

18:38.750 --> 18:40.160
I'm just concerned about you.

18:40.230 --> 18:41.160
You got it wrong that day.

18:41.160 --> 18:42.310
I didn't come out of Ming Sheng's house.

18:42.310 --> 18:43.400
You must've been mistaken.

18:43.750 --> 18:44.990
Your mom already told me.

18:45.440 --> 18:46.510
I got it wrong.

18:46.880 --> 18:48.880
Anyway,
Ming Sheng doesn't live here anymore.

18:48.960 --> 18:51.600
You two won't have anything to do
with each other anymore.

18:53.600 --> 18:54.400
Qingyu.

18:56.310 --> 18:57.600
All right. I'll get back to work.

18:57.600 --> 18:58.640
You guys go on.

19:08.230 --> 19:09.030
Mom.

19:09.200 --> 19:11.230
The school is holding a research project

19:11.230 --> 19:12.360
on wetlands.

19:12.400 --> 19:14.120
I want to go to Qingxi Wetland
this weekend

19:14.120 --> 19:15.160
with Mumu.

19:15.360 --> 19:16.600
She's about to sit for NCEE.

19:16.600 --> 19:18.230
This might help her relax
and clear her mind.

19:18.310 --> 19:19.120
All right.

19:19.710 --> 19:21.070
Keep up the hard work, you two,

19:22.400 --> 19:23.470
and don't stay out too late.

19:26.680 --> 19:27.550
Sit tight.

19:57.840 --> 19:58.440
Here you go.

20:07.360 --> 20:09.400
Why did you suddenly move?

20:09.920 --> 20:11.120
Does your dad know?

20:12.470 --> 20:13.120
Oh.

20:15.070 --> 20:16.880
I signed up for the TEF,

20:16.880 --> 20:18.070
and it includes
a closed training program

20:18.400 --> 20:19.640
with dorms.

20:19.840 --> 20:21.750
I thought studying somewhere else

20:22.200 --> 20:23.470
would help me focus.

20:23.920 --> 20:26.200
My dad's caught up in a legal case
at the hospital.

20:26.960 --> 20:28.360
He doesn't have time for me.

20:33.750 --> 20:35.710
Then why haven't you been
going to school?

20:35.710 --> 20:37.270
I haven't seen you in ages.

20:37.600 --> 20:38.640
I took leave.

20:38.920 --> 20:41.120
The teacher said
they'd check with my dad,

20:41.990 --> 20:44.230
but I figured
since he couldn't control me anyway,

20:45.030 --> 20:46.440
I'll be fine
as long as I stay out of trouble.

20:47.160 --> 20:48.790
What about you? How've you been?

20:53.270 --> 20:54.400
You look a little rough.

20:57.840 --> 20:59.030
Stop poking at it,

20:59.230 --> 21:00.790
or you'll ruin it.

21:14.360 --> 21:17.230
Here's the number for Dr. Le Fan
at the provincial hospital.

21:17.400 --> 21:19.470
She's a school friend of my dad's,
and she's really kind.

21:19.470 --> 21:20.840
She's a psychologist.

21:21.200 --> 21:22.920
If you're feeling really down,

21:23.230 --> 21:24.070
give her a call.

21:27.840 --> 21:28.880
Thanks.

21:39.680 --> 21:42.710
You should give this number
to Qiao Qingyu too.

21:45.790 --> 21:47.070
She definitely needs it.

22:13.360 --> 22:15.120
Chirpy has been with me for two months.

22:15.120 --> 22:16.680
I thought I'd let it go today

22:16.680 --> 22:18.750
since we're out.

22:21.070 --> 22:22.400
This is the bird

22:22.400 --> 22:23.710
you and Sheng rescued together, right?

22:24.840 --> 22:26.960
I saw it at Sheng's place.

22:30.160 --> 22:31.790
Sheng suddenly moved out.

22:33.600 --> 22:34.680
I heard about that.

22:37.600 --> 22:38.030
Yesterday,

22:38.030 --> 22:40.230
I saw him at the milk tea shop
near the school.

22:42.790 --> 22:45.920
He looked really down.

22:48.270 --> 22:51.070
I've known him for a long time.
I can tell.

22:51.880 --> 22:52.640
If nothing had happened

22:52.640 --> 22:54.510
between you two,

22:55.230 --> 22:56.710
he wouldn't be so heartbroken.

23:00.440 --> 23:02.640
I'm not blaming you
because I feel bad for him.

23:03.230 --> 23:04.840
I'm just a little bothered

23:04.840 --> 23:05.790
that you didn't tell me

23:06.960 --> 23:08.160
the whole story.

23:10.710 --> 23:12.680
Sheng isn't someone who overreacts.

23:12.960 --> 23:14.680
Did you say or do something

23:14.710 --> 23:16.640
that made him misunderstand?

23:19.070 --> 23:20.200
Nothing at all.

23:22.510 --> 23:24.120
Oh, forget it.

23:24.920 --> 23:26.920
No point dwelling on it.
It's all in the past now.

23:33.120 --> 23:34.960
Here's the number for Dr. Le Fan
at the provincial hospital.

23:34.960 --> 23:35.990
Keep it safe.

23:36.550 --> 23:38.360
Sheng insisted I give it to you.

23:40.160 --> 23:41.750
I don't want Sheng to worry about you.

23:48.400 --> 23:49.310
Let's do it here.

23:49.510 --> 23:50.360
All right.

24:05.070 --> 24:06.550
Why isn't Chirpy coming out?

24:07.790 --> 24:09.400
Is it because it hasn't healed yet?

24:12.470 --> 24:14.550
What kind of bird
do you think Chirpy is?

24:17.160 --> 24:19.880
It's still too young to tell right now.

24:23.640 --> 24:25.360
I hope it's an eagle.

24:25.880 --> 24:27.880
It's just too weak at the moment.

24:31.070 --> 24:34.120
One day, it will
spread its wings and fly,

24:34.710 --> 24:35.790
soaring to freedom.

24:36.920 --> 24:38.230
It will grow up.

24:43.270 --> 24:44.070
Mumu.

24:45.960 --> 24:47.230
I don't want to grow up.

24:50.550 --> 24:53.310
Growing up just means

24:53.310 --> 24:55.640
becoming the kind of adult
we don't like.

24:58.360 --> 25:00.070
Will growing up
really make things better?

25:06.270 --> 25:07.070
I don't know.

25:26.550 --> 25:27.750
Come on! Let me see!

25:29.640 --> 25:30.680
Just let me take a look.

25:30.680 --> 25:31.510
Call me dad.

25:33.440 --> 25:35.120
Dad. Now, hurry up!

25:35.160 --> 25:37.360
Ye Zilin, care to share with us?

25:37.360 --> 25:38.750
Come on, say it louder
so everyone can hear.

25:51.880 --> 25:52.600
Stop shaking.

26:04.750 --> 26:05.920
Everyone, head to the field!

26:05.990 --> 26:06.840
Quickly!

26:21.600 --> 26:22.310
Hurry!

26:24.440 --> 26:25.600
Be careful, everyone!

26:43.270 --> 26:44.470
Noodles for Table Four.

27:02.230 --> 27:04.840
A 7.8-magnitude earthquake
has struck Xichuan.

27:05.070 --> 27:07.160
Following the State Council of China's
emergency rescue deployment,

27:07.310 --> 27:09.600
the earthquake emergency
response mechanism

27:09.600 --> 27:11.120
has been urgently activated.

27:11.510 --> 27:12.990
Relevant rescue personnel

27:13.030 --> 27:16.030
and material mobilization
have been fully initiated.

27:16.510 --> 27:18.680
When one part struggles,
the others help.

27:27.400 --> 27:29.510
Donate what you can, money or supplies.

27:29.990 --> 27:31.880
When one part struggles,
the others help.

27:32.270 --> 27:34.310
Donate what you can, money or supplies.

27:36.230 --> 27:37.990
Don't rush. One at a time.

27:48.550 --> 27:50.070
We only have so much money.

27:50.310 --> 27:51.680
It's far from enough.

27:52.200 --> 27:54.680
But we've all donated
as much as we can.

27:55.400 --> 27:56.790
Why don't we go out on the streets
and raise funds?

27:56.990 --> 27:58.030
There's strength in numbers.

27:58.510 --> 28:00.070
The more people donate,
the more money we'll collect.

28:00.070 --> 28:02.440
I heard donating money
isn't helpful now.

28:02.470 --> 28:03.840
What the disaster area needs most
are supplies.

28:04.160 --> 28:04.960
That's easy.

28:05.230 --> 28:06.360
We can collect donations on the street,

28:06.360 --> 28:07.710
convert the money into supplies,

28:07.750 --> 28:09.160
and deliver them
to the disaster area ourselves.

28:09.160 --> 28:09.960
Sounds good.

28:10.070 --> 28:11.030
That works.

28:11.310 --> 28:12.160
What works?

28:17.990 --> 28:19.600
I understand your desire to help

28:19.600 --> 28:20.360
the disaster victims.

28:20.550 --> 28:21.600
But you're students

28:22.120 --> 28:24.070
whose priority is to study.

28:24.680 --> 28:25.470
But

28:25.640 --> 28:27.550
aren't we studying
so that we can serve the country?

28:27.550 --> 28:28.230
That's right.

28:28.310 --> 28:29.750
Now is the time

28:29.750 --> 28:30.200
when our country needs us.

28:30.400 --> 28:31.510
All right. Answer these questions.

28:32.360 --> 28:33.880
How much money do you think
you can collect on the streets?

28:33.960 --> 28:35.270
Do you know what supplies
are most needed

28:35.270 --> 28:36.030
in the disaster area?

28:36.960 --> 28:37.960
With transportation
to the epicenter cut off,

28:37.960 --> 28:39.600
how are you planning
to deliver the supplies?

28:39.960 --> 28:41.960
Even if you manage
to reach the disaster area,

28:42.310 --> 28:44.400
do you know how to protect yourselves
from secondary disasters?

28:44.510 --> 28:46.310
Or will you just end up needing
to be rescued yourselves?

28:54.840 --> 28:55.990
What I want to say

28:57.200 --> 28:58.200
is that society

28:58.400 --> 28:59.960
is like a precise machine.

29:00.920 --> 29:02.790
Only when everyone performs their duties

29:02.990 --> 29:05.190
can the machine operate efficiently

29:05.200 --> 29:07.310
and respond to different emergencies.

29:07.790 --> 29:09.310
One day, when you grow up,

29:09.440 --> 29:10.960
you'll become part of it.

29:10.960 --> 29:13.230
But for now,
there's only one thing you need to do.

29:13.600 --> 29:14.600
Study.

29:15.400 --> 29:16.200
Understood?

29:31.470 --> 29:31.990
All right.

29:32.510 --> 29:34.360
Turn to page 38.

29:34.920 --> 29:35.640
Let's continue with the problem

29:35.640 --> 29:37.070
we didn't finish yesterday.

29:40.600 --> 29:42.640
I've already gone over
this problem before.

29:42.640 --> 29:43.200
But half the class

29:43.200 --> 29:44.600
still got it wrong.

29:44.600 --> 29:45.360
Why?

29:45.440 --> 29:46.230
Two reasons.

29:46.400 --> 29:48.270
First, you haven't mastered

29:48.270 --> 29:49.600
the answering techniques.

29:49.710 --> 29:50.710
And two.

29:50.880 --> 29:52.120
You didn't read the question carefully.

29:52.440 --> 29:53.400
Now, I'll explain…

29:53.400 --> 29:54.750
I really misjudged Sun.

29:54.750 --> 29:56.200
I didn't expect him
to be so cold-hearted.

29:56.200 --> 29:57.920
He had no concern
for the disaster victims.

29:58.120 --> 29:59.790
Exactly. And he kept telling us

30:00.160 --> 30:01.960
that our priority is to study.

30:01.960 --> 30:03.510
I think he just looks down on us.

30:03.510 --> 30:04.790
He thinks we'll only cause trouble.

30:05.200 --> 30:07.200
I don't think Mr. Sun meant it that way.

30:07.840 --> 30:09.960
Stop defending him.

30:10.230 --> 30:12.600
That's right. We heard it ourselves.

30:14.880 --> 30:16.120
Do you guys think

30:16.120 --> 30:17.640
Sun has no personal life?

30:17.640 --> 30:19.400
I've never heard of him
having a girlfriend.

30:19.470 --> 30:21.310
Isn't that what they call a workaholic?

30:21.600 --> 30:22.310
Yes.

30:22.310 --> 30:25.070
At his age, no less. That's worrying.

30:26.550 --> 30:27.790
Ready. Go.

30:28.070 --> 30:33.440
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

30:33.440 --> 30:38.790
Two, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

30:38.790 --> 30:44.070
Three, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

30:44.230 --> 30:49.840
Four, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

30:49.840 --> 30:55.710
Five, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

30:55.990 --> 30:56.550
All right.

30:56.640 --> 30:57.990
That's it for today.

30:58.160 --> 30:59.990
On Saturday, we'll represent the school

30:59.990 --> 31:02.230
in a disaster relief charity performance
organized by the community.

31:02.440 --> 31:03.470
When you go home,

31:03.470 --> 31:06.030
practice the moves.

31:06.030 --> 31:08.360
Especially on the coordination
between the lead dancer and the group.

31:08.400 --> 31:09.920
Got it? Thank you, everyone.

31:23.880 --> 31:27.120
You're clearly a talented dancer,

31:27.790 --> 31:29.680
and you even helped me choreograph this.

31:29.790 --> 31:31.600
Why won't you join the dance club?

31:35.200 --> 31:37.230
You know Qiao Beiyu
was an amazing dancer, right?

31:40.360 --> 31:42.120
Ever since what happened to her,

31:42.880 --> 31:44.680
my mom has been prejudiced
against dancing.

31:45.360 --> 31:46.960
She thinks girls who dance

31:46.960 --> 31:48.470
are flirtatious and improper.

31:50.600 --> 31:52.120
After that big commotion,

31:52.710 --> 31:54.750
she's been paranoid about everything.

31:54.750 --> 31:56.030
She watches me like a hawk.

31:57.470 --> 31:59.160
If she finds out I'm dancing like Beiyu

31:59.160 --> 32:01.070
at this point,

32:02.030 --> 32:02.880
I can't even imagine

32:02.880 --> 32:04.400
what she'd do.

32:07.120 --> 32:08.750
Are you going to live your whole life

32:08.750 --> 32:10.510
according to your mom's wishes?

32:18.120 --> 32:19.470
Maybe it's the only way

32:20.120 --> 32:21.880
to avoid anyone getting hurt.

32:36.470 --> 32:37.990
I'm going to go for a layup.

32:37.990 --> 32:39.230
Come on. One, two!

32:42.230 --> 32:43.440
I'm not going to pick.

32:43.440 --> 32:44.550
Fake.

32:44.550 --> 32:45.600
Fake block.

32:45.600 --> 32:46.030
Fake.

32:52.990 --> 32:53.920
You scared me!

32:53.920 --> 32:54.640
What's the deal?

32:54.640 --> 32:57.120
Sun got scolded by the principal.

32:57.510 --> 32:58.360
It is Sun.

32:58.960 --> 33:00.510
Usually, it's him scolding us.

33:00.600 --> 33:02.600
Refreshing to see someone else
scolding him for once.

33:02.600 --> 33:03.310
Mm.

33:03.310 --> 33:04.200
Do you think

33:04.750 --> 33:06.470
the principal realized

33:06.510 --> 33:09.160
Sun doesn't have enough compassion
for the disaster victims,

33:09.510 --> 33:10.510
so that's why he's scolding him?

33:10.510 --> 33:11.230
Duh!

33:11.230 --> 33:11.640
Right?

33:11.640 --> 33:12.440
For sure.

33:12.790 --> 33:14.790
Mr. Sun is usually nice to everyone.

33:14.790 --> 33:16.360
You shouldn't talk about him like this.

33:18.070 --> 33:19.510
You don't get it.

33:20.120 --> 33:22.400
Sure, he's nice to us sometimes,

33:22.470 --> 33:24.200
but ignoring all those people
suffering after the disaster?

33:24.200 --> 33:25.400
That's a huge moral problem.

33:25.640 --> 33:27.360
We can't ignore big rights and wrongs

33:27.440 --> 33:28.440
just because of small favors.

33:28.440 --> 33:30.360
- Yes.
- That's right.

33:31.160 --> 33:32.920
I don't think he's from Huanzhou.

33:34.360 --> 33:35.310
So what?

33:35.310 --> 33:36.920
Don't change the topic, will you?

33:37.120 --> 33:38.920
When I was handing in my homework today,

33:38.920 --> 33:40.550
I overheard
the homeroom teacher for Class 4 say

33:40.750 --> 33:42.710
that Mr. Sun's parents
are still in the disaster area,

33:42.710 --> 33:44.160
and they haven't been able
to contact them.

33:46.400 --> 33:47.920
All right. It's time for class.

33:47.920 --> 33:48.920
Let's go. Come on.

33:49.310 --> 33:50.120
Let's go.

34:08.520 --> 34:11.320
[Chemistry Laboratory (5)]

34:25.880 --> 34:26.710
Stand up.

34:28.070 --> 34:31.070
- Good morning, Mr. Sun.
- Good morning, Mr. Sun.

34:37.679 --> 34:38.469
Please sit down.

34:45.440 --> 34:46.600
Who's on duty today?

34:46.600 --> 34:47.710
The podium is so clean.

34:59.510 --> 35:03.120
Why are you all so quiet today?

35:10.510 --> 35:11.680
Did you get into trouble again

35:11.680 --> 35:13.400
and now you're trying to make up for it?
Class Monitor?

35:16.640 --> 35:17.310
Mr. Sun.

35:17.710 --> 35:18.510
Yes?

35:21.640 --> 35:24.510
We'll pay close attention
in your class from now on.

35:26.640 --> 35:28.030
And no one is allowed

35:28.030 --> 35:29.840
to joke about Mr. Sun anymore.

35:32.960 --> 35:33.880
That's all I have to say.

35:34.610 --> 35:36.530
Mr. Sun, you have our utmost respect.

35:51.840 --> 35:53.510
Everyone, turn

35:55.170 --> 35:56.210
to page 90.

36:28.240 --> 36:29.070
Pass the ball!

36:29.070 --> 36:29.720
Here.

36:36.280 --> 36:37.280
Nice shot!

36:38.150 --> 36:38.670
Are we done?

36:38.920 --> 36:39.470
Another round?

36:39.470 --> 36:39.920
Got to go.

36:39.920 --> 36:41.960
- Bye.
- See you.

36:44.960 --> 36:46.360
Want some water, Hao?

36:46.360 --> 36:47.670
Yes, please.

36:48.280 --> 36:48.960
Sheng.

36:56.400 --> 36:57.880
That medical dispute involving your dad

36:58.280 --> 36:59.920
has been causing an uproar online.

37:00.030 --> 37:01.440
I heard about it too.

37:01.440 --> 37:03.400
They are saying
Dr. Ming is a heartless doctor,

37:03.510 --> 37:06.630
that he over-treated patients for profit
and even caused someone to die.

37:06.630 --> 37:08.030
It's pretty intense.

37:09.760 --> 37:09.960
Hey.

37:09.960 --> 37:12.070
We both think it's nonsense.

37:12.240 --> 37:13.920
We have complete faith
in your dad's character.

37:15.760 --> 37:17.470
What happens to him
has nothing to do with me.

37:17.550 --> 37:18.320
There, there.

37:18.320 --> 37:18.990
Cut it out.

37:19.240 --> 37:20.440
Speak of the devil.

37:22.070 --> 37:22.590
Mr. Ming.

37:24.320 --> 37:26.360
Sheng, see you around.

37:26.590 --> 37:27.590
Goodbye, Mr. Ming.

37:27.590 --> 37:28.360
Bye.

37:34.840 --> 37:35.840
Why haven't you been coming home

37:36.190 --> 37:37.320
and answering my calls?

37:38.110 --> 37:39.760
Didn't Sun call you?

37:39.800 --> 37:41.670
I've enrolled
in an intensive French training course.

37:42.240 --> 37:43.400
I'll be living there

37:43.840 --> 37:44.630
from now until the exam.

37:44.630 --> 37:45.760
Shouldn't you have called me yourself

37:45.760 --> 37:47.280
to tell me this?

37:47.840 --> 37:49.070
Don't you care
that I'd be worried about you?

37:49.070 --> 37:50.880
And did you ever talk to me
about your case?

37:54.960 --> 37:55.550
Oh.

37:57.590 --> 37:59.800
If you're referring
to the medical incident,

38:00.240 --> 38:02.070
well, it really came up unexpectedly.

38:02.400 --> 38:04.800
I just haven't had the chance
to tell you yet.

38:04.920 --> 38:05.840
Besides that.

38:07.960 --> 38:09.280
Why didn't you tell me it wasn't you

38:11.150 --> 38:12.470
who drove my mom away?

38:13.960 --> 38:14.630
I…

38:19.150 --> 38:19.880
Sheng,

38:21.110 --> 38:22.440
I think some things

38:23.470 --> 38:25.360
are better left unsaid.

38:26.360 --> 38:27.630
You misled me.

38:29.190 --> 38:31.150
I hated the wrong person like a fool.

38:33.320 --> 38:34.880
Does it amuse you to see that?

38:37.920 --> 38:38.920
You could've explained everything

38:38.920 --> 38:40.150
with just a few words.

38:42.440 --> 38:43.470
Do you enjoy torturing yourself?

38:44.920 --> 38:45.800
From now on,

38:46.590 --> 38:47.800
if you don't tell me about your matters,

38:48.030 --> 38:49.030
then don't bother trying
to know mine either.

38:49.880 --> 38:50.960
Just mind your own business.

39:20.960 --> 39:21.840
What are you doing?

39:22.030 --> 39:22.630
Qingyu.

39:22.630 --> 39:24.240
Have you seen my MP3 player?

39:24.670 --> 39:26.550
I told you
not to leave your stuff lying around.

39:26.550 --> 39:27.990
You'll never find it when you need it.

39:29.630 --> 39:30.320
Here.

39:42.220 --> 39:44.510
[Sender: Huanzhou People's Hospital]
[Recipient: Qiao Qingyu]

39:45.280 --> 39:47.070
Why is my mail with you?

39:48.470 --> 39:49.670
Oh, I remember now.

39:49.670 --> 39:50.960
You weren't home that day,

39:50.960 --> 39:52.760
so I accepted it for you.

39:53.510 --> 39:54.320
But

39:54.720 --> 39:57.190
I put it aside and forgot about it.

40:07.990 --> 40:08.910
[Huanzhou People's Hospital
Nursing Record]

40:08.920 --> 40:09.760
[Patient: Qiao Beiyu]

40:09.760 --> 40:11.590
This is Qiao Beiyu's medical record.

40:20.040 --> 40:23.020
[Blood test indicators normal]

40:24.780 --> 40:26.840
[Condition under control]

40:26.840 --> 40:30.550
Qiao Beiyu passed away
on the last Chinese New Year's Eve.

40:31.190 --> 40:33.800
But according to this record,

40:34.880 --> 40:36.960
her condition was stable in December

40:37.160 --> 40:39.920
of the year before.

40:40.990 --> 40:44.630
From stable to gone,

40:44.630 --> 40:46.720
it was less than two months.

40:46.800 --> 40:47.920
That's way too fast.

40:48.470 --> 40:50.800
Do you think

40:50.960 --> 40:52.590
her death wasn't inevitable,

40:52.840 --> 40:54.070
but rather a choice?

41:25.520 --> 41:29.210
♪Perhaps♪

41:29.720 --> 41:35.420
♪The more we care,
the more careful we become♪

41:36.560 --> 41:41.960
♪Counting the distance
that separates us♪

41:42.960 --> 41:48.520
♪A single step,
and we'd be closer still♪

41:54.190 --> 41:57.860
♪In the future♪

41:58.320 --> 42:04.040
♪Time will reveal this secret♪

42:05.540 --> 42:10.610
♪Waiting is a silent promise♪

42:11.860 --> 42:17.020
♪That never expires♪

42:20.620 --> 42:25.090
♪Turns out that what's on my mind♪

42:26.090 --> 42:29.760
♪Is your name♪

42:30.260 --> 42:35.360
♪The only stubbornness in my heart♪

42:36.440 --> 42:39.660
♪At first sight♪

42:40.090 --> 42:43.370
♪The future has been determined♪

42:44.060 --> 42:49.620
♪Dreams began to feel real♪

42:50.720 --> 42:54.260
♪Turns out that what's on your mind♪

42:54.720 --> 42:58.660
♪Is a place♪

42:58.960 --> 43:04.520
♪Where the same story is held dear♪

43:05.190 --> 43:08.560
♪Fortunately, I'm not sensible enough♪

43:08.890 --> 43:12.360
♪Courage wasn't late too♪

43:12.890 --> 43:18.960
♪Only then does time not betray
our acquaintance♪
